Kenya&rsquo;s rugby talent production house Menengai High School from Nakuru start their title defence against Longisa of Bomet as the Rift Valley Secondary School Sports Association Term 2A Games kick off today in Eldoret.Menengai, who won the Davies Cup 15-a-side this year after beating Chavakali High School, are drawn in Pool &lsquo;C&rsquo; which also has Chepkorniswo from West Pokot while Uasin Gishu&rsquo;s Kipsangui, Friends Bwake (Trans Nzoia) and Narok High (Narok) are in Pool &lsquo;A&rsquo;.Pool &lsquo;B&rsquo; has Kabianga (Kericho), Baringo Boys (Baringo) and Kapsabet Boys (Nandi) while Nkaimurunya (Kajiado), Simotwo (Elgeyo Marakwet) and Nanyuki Boys of Laikipia are in Pool &lsquo;D&rsquo;.Menengai has a long list of rugby accomplishments having won the inaugural 10-a-side Kahi Challenge Cup in Chavakali, Vihiga County in 2013 and reached the sevens nationals for the first time in 12 years and finished 9th overall in that year.In 2014, they emerged victorious at the 15s Davis Cup challenge held in Nakuru as well as featuring in the national games in both 7s and 15s versions placing third and seventh respectively.In boys&rsquo; handball, former national champions Kitany Boys start as favourites in Pool &lsquo;B&rsquo; against Ziwani of Laikipia, Athinai (Nakuru) and Roborwo of Bomet while Pool &lsquo;A&rsquo; has Ortum from West Pokot, Sanika (Nandi) and Sinyereni of TransNzoia.Wamba Boys of Samburu will meet Nakeel (Kajiado) and Ainabkoi of Uasin Gishu in Pool &lsquo;C&rsquo; as Koibarak (Baringo) face, Ololunga (Narok), Eliye Boys (Turkana) and Kiptere from Kericho in Pool &lsquo;D&rsquo;.Rift Valley Secondary Schools Sports Association chairman, Kipchumba Maiyo, is optimistic that the region will produce the best teams that will sail through in the national games.&ldquo;We are very optimistic that our teams will do well in the games. Our focus is to get the best that will shine during the national secondary school games,&rdquo; said Maiyo.He called on the players to observe discipline throughout the competition.Opening ceremony will be held today at Hill School with athletics set to start at 11am at Kipchoge Keino Stadium.